messages.contents: 15 Minute Resistance Band Workout
messages.name: Cindi Oakey

messages.contents: So this resistance band workout has a lot of butt leg moves which is just how most resistance band workouts will be‚Ä¶.you know what to do to keep yourself safe, right?  Small range of motion and focus on moving super slow and holding it for at least a full long breath and super slow release.  Keep your thigh feeling pulled into your hip especially when the foot is reaching away.  Skip what feels bad.  Also, let me know if you have those long elastic bands?  If yes, then there‚Äôs a lot more non lower body moves we can do, and I‚Äôll find a good video for it.  I think the Blogilates girl (the video I assigned) is cute, and she‚Äôs been doing this for a LONG time so respect her.

about.about: 6/20/22 CT intake: High Priority, 70yrs, generally keep her in the front on caddy/reformer/ladder barrel, or in the back space on allegro reformer - well distanced from other clients and help to maintain some privacy and get her in and out of the studio comfortably.  Has been doing Pilates her whole life with all kinds of teachers, also does some yoga and loves dance. Lots of likes and dislikes. Does not handle noise well - likes a zen environment and some quiet pauses when teaching her - tell her what to do and how many reps, but do not excessively cue her and leave some quiet pauses. typical celebrity protocols - do not ask her about her work or recognize her celebrity even if she is chatty and brings it up, be friendly but keep answers short and session focused on her needs, she may or may not want to work hard - ask, she generally does not like the hard stuff like the 100, challenging core work, teasers or too much head up, but she needs some core work so sneak some in. Likes extension and rotation - big stretchy feel good moves after she is warmed up.  Loves anything with magic circle, short spine, roll up, push through, elephant, front splits, eves lunge, sand bag exercises to strengthen wrists and keep bone, frog and leg circles, running, footwork, pelvic lift.  Does not like side splits where standing on reformer (feels to unsteady) semi circle or anything with feet on the push through bar.  Be careful of her tree on the short box - she moves way too fast and without proper engagement/articulation.  Skip side sit-ups on short box - always bad form.  Be careful if she is wearing her slippery ballet shoes - they are terrible but she insists.  Don‚Äôt challenge her balance in any position where she could fall.  Nothing unstable.  A well rounded strong beginner/intermediate workout with some core work but lots of feel good moves.  She is fine incorporating some old fashioned mat work too.  She is up for anything but likes the basics too.
